4 Article – Education
5 11–1701.
6 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
7 (b) “Emergency assistance” means immediate direct assistance provided by a
8 hunger–free campus to any student facing an unanticipated financial crisis or hardship.
9 (c) “Hunger–free campus” means a campus of any 4–year public institution of
10 higher education or regional higher education center that meets the requirements of §
11 11–1703(a) of this subtitle or any 2–year public institution of higher education that meets
12 the requirements of § 11–1703(b) of this subtitle.
13 (d) “Program” means the Hunger–Free Campus Grant Program.
14 11–1702.
15 (a) There is a Hunger–Free Campus Grant Program.
16 (b) The purpose of the Program is to:
17 (1) Address student hunger;
18 (2) Leverage more sustainable solutions to address basic food needs on
19 campus;
20 (3) Raise awareness of services currently offered on campus that address
21 basic food needs; and
22 (4) Build strategic partnerships at the local, State, and national levels to
23 address food insecurity among students.
24 (c) (1) The Commission shall administer the Program.
25 (2) The Commission shall develop the form to be used for the annual
26 student survey required under § 11–1703 of this subtitle.
27 11–1703.
28 (a) The Commission shall designate as a hunger–free campus any campus of a
29 4–year public institution of higher education or regional higher education center that:

